&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;docker build -t &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;ownport.github.io&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; .
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;docker run -ti --rm --name &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;blog&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -v &lt;span class="si"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;pwd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;/blog:/data/blog ownport.github.io
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Publishing to GitHub&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://help.github.com/categories/20/articles"&gt;GitHub Pages&lt;/a&gt; offer an easy and convenient way to publish Pelican sites. There are &lt;a href="https://help.github.com/articles/user-organization-and-project-pages"&gt;two types of GitHub Pages&lt;/a&gt;: Project Pages and User Pages. Pelican sites can be published as both Project Pages and User Pages.&lt;/p&gt;
